<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-16788] camel-kamelet - Local parameters get overridden by environment variable</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-16788</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a Kamelet declares a parameter like &quot;namespace&quot; or &quot;port&quot;, then the value assigned to that parameter via properties is ignored if there&apos;s a &quot;NAMESPACE&quot; or &quot;PORT&quot; environment variable set on the host.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That strategy may work well for global parameters, but scoped parameters should prioritize the local configuration if present.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
